      "writtenOn": "2021-06-24T09:46:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As you may know, today, there are two mechanisms for test bundles to pass initialization parameters to the framework:\n\n1. testing.Registry (i.e. testing.AddTest, testing.AddFixture, ...)\n2. bundle.Delegate (passed to bundle.LocalDefault/RemoteDefault in the bundlemain package)\n\nWhen adding a new initialization parameter (in this case, valid runtime variables), which mechanism to use depends on the characteristics of the new parameter.\n\n- With testing.Registry, registrations can be split across many files (e.g. testing.AddTest is called in many files). This is useful if there are many users adding/modifying/removing registrations and conflicts are expected if registrations are put in a single file.\n- With bundle.Delegate, we have only one place where parameters are configured (the bundlemain package). This is useful if we want to keep all registrations in a single place.\n\nSo, in the case of runtime variables, IMO:\n\n- If runtime variable definitions scatter across files, we should use testing.Registry\n- If runtime variable definitions stay in a single file, we should use bundle.Delegate",
      "revId": "3bd2f490ee633b1f395d7d1c9e35e635ceb7235a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
